<article class="blog--container blog-preview">
<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2015/05/19/springone2gx-2014-replay-philosophical-architecture-in-grails">SpringOne2GX 2014 Replay: Philosophical Architecture in Grails </a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon news-and-events"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/news">News and Events</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/c910c2f6520a5977a836d74e86e07cb4?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Pieter Humphrey</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2015-05-19 17:02:00.0">May 19, 2015</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="2131" href="/blog/2015/05/19/springone2gx-2014-replay-philosophical-architecture-in-grails#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Recorded at SpringOne2GX 2014. </p>
<p>Speaker: David Dawson, Simplicity Itself </p>
<p>G&amp;G Special Topics </p>
<p>Slides: <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/s2gx-philosophicalarchitecture">http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/s2gx-philosophicalarchitecture</a></p>
<p>Software development is hard. Life is hard. We try to keep up with a changing world, and it's hard. Where though, does the problem lie? In this talk, David, CEO at Simplicity Itself, will describe a different way of approaching the problem of software development, a different way of trying to keep up with a changing world. This is not a soft talk, all opinions are backed up by cold hard code in a running Grails application, showing how a change in the way you think can radically change your software.</p>
</div>
</section>
<a class="blog-preview--readmore desktop-only" href="/blog/2015/05/19/springone2gx-2014-replay-philosophical-architecture-in-grails">
Read more...
</a>
</article>
