<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Recorded at SpringOne2GX 2014. </p>
<p>Speaker: Kenneth Kousen </p>
<p>G&amp;G Special Topics </p>
<p>Slides: <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/groovy-vampires">http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/groovy-vampires</a></p>
<p>If a book as horrible as Twilight can sell millions of copies and be made into an even worse movie, how many copies can a book with Groovy vampires sell? (Spoiler: Not as many.) Yes, this topic may be silly, but the technologies used (Groovy, Ratpack, MongoDB, Grails, REST) are (un)deadly serious. </p>
